      "body" : "I don't think it's so much the review burden. In a separate tool we also have the review burden, as it would be built from the same source.\r\n\r\nSending queries over RPC to `bitcoind` is just fundamentally stupid for context-free utlity operations. They can be computed by a library/binary running on the client side, or be performed by simple services that are orders of magnitude cheaper to run than `bitcoind`.",
